 <center> 
  <h1><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Background (Dexter Hypertext Model)</font></h1> 
 </center> 
 
<p><br>
  <font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>The Dexter Hypertext 
  Model</strong></font></p>
<ul>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">was developed during two small 
    workshops, the first of which was held in 1988 at the Dexter Inn in New Hampshire 
    (thus the model's name) </font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">sought to develop a common terminology 
    for the hypertext field</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">is an attempt to capture and formalize 
    the abstractions common to hypertext systems</font></li>
</ul>
<p><font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Three layers of 
  the Dexter model</strong></font></p>
<ul>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">run-time layer</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">storage layer</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">with-in component layer</font></li>
</ul>
